## Deobfuscated Code

```javascript
// Constants
var TAU = 6.283;          // ≈ 2π
var PHI = 1.618;          // Golden ratio
var SQRT1_2 = 0.707;      // ≈ √(1/2)

// Configuration parameters
var config = {
    parameterA: 4000,       // Repulsion strength between all nodes
    parameterB: 0.004,      // Default spring constant for edges
    parameterC: 0.92,       // Velocity damping/friction factor
    constantD: 0.0003,      // Gravity/centering force strength
    limitE: 40,             // Maximum number of particles
    rateF: 0.04,            // Particle velocity decay rate
    valueG: 0.06            // Camera/viewport smoothing factor
};

// --- NODES ---
var nodes = [
    { id: "hub",       label: "Hub",        r: 26, x: 400, y: 300, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "alpha",     label: "Alpha",      r: 16, x: 500, y: 200, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "beta",      label: "Beta",       r: 16, x: 300, y: 400, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "gamma",     label: "Gamma",      r: 14, x: 250, y: 180, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "delta",     label: "Delta",      r: 14, x: 550, y: 380, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "epsilon",   label: "Epsilon",    r: 12, x: 350, y: 150, vx: 0, vy: 0 }
];

// --- EDGES (springs) ---
var edges = [
    { a: "hub", b: "alpha",   rest: 160, k: 0.006 },
    { a: "hub", b: "beta",    rest: 160, k: 0.005 },
    { a: "hub", b: "gamma",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: "hub", b: "delta",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: "hub", b: "epsilon", rest: 180, k: 0.003 },
    { a: "alpha", b: "beta",    rest: 200, k: 0.002 },
    { a: "gamma", b: "delta",   rest: 220, k: 0.002 },
    { a: "alpha", b: "epsilon", rest: 200, k: 0.002 }
];

// --- CAMERA ---
var camera = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
var cameraTarget = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };

// --- PARTICLES ---
var particles = [];
var frameCount = 0;

// Find a node by ID
function findNode(id) {
    for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
    }
    return null;
}

// Physics simulation step
function simulate() {
    // 1) Node-node REPULSION (Coulomb-like force)
    for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        for (var j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
            var dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
            var dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
            var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
            var force = config.parameterA / (dist * dist);
            var fx = (dx / dist) * force;
            var fy = (dy / dist) * force;
            nodes[i].vx += fx;
            nodes[i].vy += fy;
            nodes[j].vx -= fx;
            nodes[j].vy -= fy;
        }
    }

    // 2) Edge SPRING attraction (Hooke's law)
    for (var e = 0; e < edges.length; e++) {
        var nodeA = findNode(edges[e].a);
        var nodeB = findNode(edges[e].b);
        if (!nodeA || !nodeB) continue;

        var dx = nodeB.x - nodeA.x;
        var dy = nodeB.y - nodeA.y;
        var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
        var displacement = dist - edges[e].rest;
        var force = (edges[e].k || config.parameterB) * displacement;

        nodeA.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeA.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
    }

    // 3) Apply DAMPING, GRAVITY toward center (400, 300), and update positions
    for (var n = 0; n < nodes.length; n++) {
        nodes[n].vx += (400 - nodes[n].x) * config.constantD;  // centering force
        nodes[n].vy += (300 - nodes[n].y) * config.constantD;
        nodes[n].vx *= config.parameterC;  // friction/damping
        nodes[n].vy *= config.parameterC;
        nodes[n].x += nodes[n].vx;         // integrate position
        nodes[n].y += nodes[n].vy;
    }
}

// Spawn a new particle from a random node
function spawnParticle() {
    if (particles.length >= config.limitE) return;

    var sourceNode = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
    var angle = Math.random() * TAU;
    var speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * SQRT1_2;

    particles.push({
        x: sourceNode.x,
        y: sourceNode.y,
        vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
        vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
        age: 0,
        maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
        size: 0.8 + Math.random() * PHI * SQRT1_2
    });
}

// Update and cull particles
function updateParticles() {
    for (var i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        var p = particles[i];
        p.vx *= 1 - config.rateF * 0.125;   // gentle drag
        p.vy *= 1 - config.rateF * 0.125;
        p.x += p.vx;
        p.y += p.vy;
        p.age++;
        if (p.age > p.maxAge) {
            particles.splice(i, 1);           // remove dead particles
        }
    }
}

// Smooth camera interpolation toward target
function updateCamera() {
    camera.x += (cameraTarget.x - camera.x) * config.valueG;
    camera.y += (cameraTarget.y - camera.y) * config.valueG;
    camera.zoom += (cameraTarget.zoom - camera.zoom) * config.valueG;
}

// Main loop tick
function tick() {
    simulate();
    updateParticles();
    updateCamera();
    if (frameCount % 3 === 0) spawnParticle();  // spawn particle every 3rd frame
    frameCount++;
}

setInterval(tick, 16);  // ~60 FPS
```

## What It Does

This is a **force-directed graph layout engine** with decorative particles. Specifically:

### 🔵 Graph Physics (Force-Directed Layout)
- **6 nodes** ("Hub", "Alpha", "Beta", "Gamma", "Delta", "Epsilon") connected by **8 edges** form a network graph
- **Repulsion**: Every pair of nodes pushes each other apart (inverse-square law, like electric charges) — prevents overlap
- **Spring attraction**: Connected nodes are pulled together by Hooke's law springs, each with a configurable rest length and stiffness (`k`)
- **Centering gravity**: All nodes are gently pulled toward the center point (400, 300)
- **Damping**: Velocity is multiplied by 0.92 each frame (friction) so the system settles to equilibrium

### ✨ Particle System
- Every 3 frames, a particle spawns from a **random node** and drifts outward at a random angle
- Particles slowly decelerate and are removed after their `maxAge` (800–2000 frames)
- Maximum of **40 particles** at a time
- This creates a visual "sparkle" or "aura" effect around the graph

### 📷 Smooth Camera
- A camera with `x`, `y`, `zoom` smoothly interpolates (lerps) toward a target position at 6% per frame
- This would allow smooth panning/zooming if the target is updated (e.g., by user interaction — not included in this snippet)

### 🎯 Summary
> **This is the simulation/physics backend for an animated, interactive force-directed network graph visualization with ambient particle effects and smooth camera movement, running at ~60 FPS.** There's no rendering code here — this is purely the data/logic layer that would feed into a Canvas or SVG renderer.
